Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Denver Energy Center is comprised of two towers, Joule (1675-Tower 1) 382,752 square feet and Ohm (1625-Tower 2) 402,797 square feet totaling 785,549 square feet in Denverâ€™s Central Business District.  The property is situated in downtown Denver and ideally positioned at the corner of 16th Street and Broadway.  The project is easily accessible from all of Denver and offers tenants direct access to nearby amenities including the 16th Street Mall and the Denver Pavilions.  

Denver Energy Center offers a full-service experience to its tenants and visitors from the moment one arrives at the building.  The on-site amenities include a start of the art conference/training center, a full-service fitness center with towel service, banks, bike storage, 24/7 security, premium secure parking, class A lobby, landscaped courtyard with ample seating and onsite property management.
